# Day 0 – Python Refresh

Today marked the beginning of my DSA journey using Python. Instead of jumping straight into data structures and algorithms, I spent time refreshing the Python fundamentals I had learned before.

## Topics Reviewed

* Lists vs Tuples
* Sets and Dictionaries
* `==` vs `is`
* `for` loops with `range()`
* `if`, `elif`, `else`
* Functions and `return`
* Finding the largest element in a list
* Counting character frequency (concept)
* Even/Odd number logic using the modulo operator

## What I Learned

* Lists are mutable, while tuples are immutable.
* Sets store unique values and automatically remove duplicates.
* `==` compares values, while `is` checks whether two variables refer to the same object.
* Python `for` loops use `range()` instead of C-style loops.
* Functions should return values when the result needs to be used later.
* My problem-solving skills are better than my Python syntax, so my focus will be on rebuilding Python fluency through consistent practice.

## Goal

Build a strong Python foundation before moving into Data Structures and Algorithms, solving a few problems every day and understanding every solution instead of memorizing it.
